The Productions tab provides an overview of all Pvideo Productions, both static and dynamic. It consists of three main areas:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Top toolbar** with **search field** and **action button** to start a new Production

- **Tab selector** for dynamic and static Productions

- **Table area **containing all existing Productions for the selected type

The table in the Productions tab contains the following columns:

Field

Description

**Origin**

Environment from which the Production has been triggered:

- **Pvideo Designer:** Triggered from within the Video Designer application.

- **Doxee Platform:** Triggered through a Batch or On-Demand Workflows task.

> Tip

Hover over the **help icon** to view and copy the **step ID** and **tenant **name.

- **API:** Triggered through an API endpoint.

**Name**

Name and UUID of the Production

**Project**

Name of the Project and associated data schema

**Input**

Source of the dynamic data (only for dynamic Productions)

**Start**

Date and time when the Production was triggered

**Status**

Status of the Production:

- **Draft:** The Production process has been started but not finalized.

- **Completed:** The Production process has been finalized and the Pvideo output has been produced.

- **Failed:** The Production process has been finalized but was unable to produce a Pvideo output. Check the 

> Tip: Sort and search

The Productions table can be searched and sorted to easily find a particular Production. Use the full-text search field to search the columns **Origin**, **Name**, **Project**, **Input **and **Start**.

Click on a column header to sort that column in ascending or descending order. Click again to change the sorting or return to the default sorting.

## User actions on Productions
The following actions can be performed from the Productions tab:

- **Create a new Production **by clicking the **New Production** button

- **Edit a Production draft** by clicking the **Edit** button (appears on mouseover)

- **Delete a Production draft** by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Delete**

- **View the output** of a finished Production by clicking the **View **button (appears on mouseover)

- **Download the output** of a finished Production by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Download output**

- **Inspect the page **of a failed Production by clicking the **View **button (appears on mouseover)

- **Download the log **of a failed Production by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Download errors log**
